No.

Bruiser's are a class of champions that cannot function on low econ.

They need gold for big items like {{item:3078}} {{item:3053}} {{item:3748}} 

&nbsp;

This is the reason you don't see champions like {{champion:164}} or {{champion:39}} being played as Support.

They may have good lockdown, damage and chase potential in their kit but they need big items to be champions.

&nbsp;

Kayle is another "fighter" that I'd say is unviable as a Support.

She needs big items and levels to become a champion.

Kayle will never be able to hit her level 11 and 16 dream when she is splitting experience.

Yes but braum`s ult kind of redeems him after lvl 6  since its an aoe knockup.

Also braum can stack his passive on multiple enemies thanks to the fact that his teammates can finish the proc for him, tahm kench can only stack on 1 or 2 enemies (if he is lucky), and even then he can only cc one person at a time, using his w just means he takes the stacks off of them and his allies cant attack them in his w.....so he is stuck just using his q 

w use is extremely niche since you actually lose dps due to the stack removal, the damage isn't worth it and the enemy is in your belly and cannot be attacked by allies unless you happen to have someone like {{champion:9}}
